<paragraph blockId="57.[182,1390,293,794]" box="[182,656,485,514]" pageId="57" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[182,417,485,514]" pageId="57" pageNumber="334">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[183,1123,521,554]" pageId="57" pageNumber="334" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="57.[182,1390,293,794]" box="[183,1123,521,554]" pageId="57" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[183,884,521,554]" pageId="57" pageNumber="334">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="334" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="57.[182,1390,293,794]" pageId="57" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[184,536,561,594]" pageId="57" pageNumber="334">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Not assessed on The IUCN Red List as a distinct species. Distribution of the Portuguese Field Vole is small, but it was the second most abundant vole retrieved from owl pellets in northern Portugal, where it was classified as “not threatened.”
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
